The paper deals with distributed computing and graph problems, which are typical topics in the Distributed Computing (cs.DC) and Discrete Mathematics (cs.DM) sub-categories. The use of automata theory to analyze the problems suggests that the paper may also be relevant to the Computational Complexity (cs.CC) and Logic in Computer Science (cs.LO) sub-categories. Finally, the paper's focus on algorithm synthesis and optimization suggests that it may also be relevant to the Formal Languages and Automata Theory (cs.FL) sub-category.
